  "notes": [
    "<s><b>Prerequisites:</b> Shown in parenthesis under course name</s>",
    "<b>Writing Intensive Courses:</b> 3 are required: 1st year = URWT 150/ISTE 110 + 1 Gen Ed course + program specific (CSCI-472 Historical & Current Perspectives in Computer Science)",
    "<b>Lab Sciences:</b> Only specific sequences are allowed in Biology, Chemistry or Physics; please see the CS handbook",
    "<b>CS/SE BS/MS Double-Counted Courses:</b> are noted with an *.",
    "<b><u>Note that if 1, 2 or 3 CSCI graduate (cluster) electives are taken to satisfy SE Graduate Elective requirements, correspondingly 1, 2 or 3 of the double-count courses can be moved from Open Elective and subbed in to satisfy CSCI (cluster) electives</u></b>",
    "<b>Starting in Fall 2025, the MS in Software Engineering requires a 2-course Project (SWEN-783 and SWEN-784), expected to be taken as a Fall/Spring sequence</b>"
